<code>align-let.el</code> aligns values in a Lisp <code>let</code> form, and related <code>let*</code> etc.  Get it from

: http://user42.tuxfamily.org/align-let/index.html

For example

    (let ((x 1)
          (foo   2)
          (zz (blah)))
      ...)

becomes

    (let ((x   1)
          (foo 2)
          (zz  (blah)))
      ...)

Multi-var <code>setq</code> is aligned similarly too,

    (setq x   1
          foo 2
          zz  (blah))

----
